SIMPLE: scapular
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scapular
<hw>Scap"u*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>scapulaire</ets>. Cf. <er>Scapulary</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to the scapula or the shoulder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Scapular arch</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>, <cd>the
pectoral arch. See under <er>pectoral</er>.</cd> --
<mcol><col><b>Scapular region</b></col>, <it>or</it> <col><b>Scapular
tract</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a definite longitudinal
area over the shoulder and along each side of the back of a bird, from
which the scapular feathers arise.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scapular</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scapular
<hw>Scap"u*lar</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of a
special group of feathers which arise from each of the scapular regions
and lie along the sides of the back.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scapulary</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Scapular</ent>⟦br⟧
